events.name: Android for Work - Introduction and Codelab
events.description:
Android for Work allows developers to build apps that take advantage of security and management features built into Android, to help employees be more productive in scenarios such as BYOD (bring your own device) and COSU (corporate-owned single-use) devices.

Agenda:
09:30 - 10:00 Welcome and intro to Android for Work [VIDEO]
10:00 - 10:45 New APIs in M, Work and Life, Enterprise Ready App, Single Use Devices, Android for Work for Developers [VIDEO]
10:45 - 11:00 Break
11:00 - 12:00 Achieving Single Sign-on with AppAuth [CODELAB]
12:00 - 12:15 Break
12:15 - 13:00 Build Applications for Single Use Devices [CODELAB]

events.name: Monthly GDG-Meetup
events.description:
We will begin with a short tour of introductions.

Afterwards, there will be a 1h live programming session using Android Studio. I will try to answer your questions on how to implement & realize your ideas during this session.

Finally, we'll have a social evening. We might just move to the "Schlappen" around the corner.

events.name: GDG-Meetup: AppEngine trial
events.description: We will talk about the features and possibilities provided by Google AppEngine, a powerful platform to build apps and scale automatically. Furthermore, topics will be: User Authentication, AppEngine side languages (Java, Python, PHP, Go), NoSQL Datastore, Memcache and Logging. After the talk and discussion, you're invited to join us for a beer at the Schachtel (pub around the corner).

events.name: What's new in Android N
events.description:
With Android 7.0 Nougat, we can take advantage of new developer features such as multi-window support, direct reply, notification enhancements, extended doze mode, direct boot, and more.

We will talk, watch videos and slides about the following topics:

What's new in Android N Multi-Window, Notifications, Drag'n Drop in Android N Project Volta (Android Battery Life) Jack compiler I'll try to organize a little surprise for everyone :)

events.name: Next ’17 Extended Viewing Party
events.description:
Join us for a viewing party of Google Cloud Next '17!

Next ‘17 will be the largest event in Google’s history. Google Cloud engineers, customers and partners will gather for inspiration and hands on experiences with tools, technologies and services born in the Cloud, including the latest developments from Google Cloud Platform, G Suite, Maps and Devices.

After watching the keynote, we will choose together which sessions of the Next '17 schedule we'll watch. Please also feel free to vote for a session by leaving a comment here.

My House of Marley Audio System will provide good sound and we'll have a cozy cinema atmosphere in the office of Tomes. There will also be drinks and food (Pizza) and we'll have a break after each session. 

You're free to come for only one or two sessions as well if you want.
events.how_to_find_us: The office is located opposite the B31 from Café Extrablatt. It's in the third upper floor on the left.

events.name: Open Discussion and Networking
events.description:
Hello everyone! We will have an open developer discussion and lunch all together at the round table @ Brasil, Freiburg.

The goals of this meetup are the following: 
1. Collect all your topics of interest. 
2. Elect speakers for talks about those topics. 
3. Learn to know each other & connect!

Agenda:

12.00 Introduction
12.15 Collection of topics and interests
12.45 Lunch
13.30 Vote for speakers and talks
14.00 Conclusion
events.how_to_find_us: Find us at a big table in the non-smoker area :)

events.name: Golang-Meetup hosted by iTernity
events.description:
Schedule:
19.00: Snacks & Sixpacks 
20.00: Talk „5 years of Go - My personal highlights.“ von „Go-Pro“ Oliver Eilhard 
20.30: Diskussion & Networking

Abstract:
Die Programmiersprache Golang (aka Go) gibt es nun schon seit mindestens fünf Jahren. Die quelloffene Sprache wurde von den Robert Griesemer, Rob Pike und Ken Thompson erfunden und hat eine sehr aktive Community. Golang hat eine mit C vergleichbare Laufzeitperformance bietet aber gleichzeitig ein automatisches Memory-Management an. Concurrency ist als First-Class-Citizen in Form von Goroutines und Channels direkt in die Sprache eingebettet. Darüber hinaus werden Tools wie Code-Formating, Test-Runner, Benchmarking, Code-Coverage oder Profiling direkt mit geliefert. Trotz der vielen Vorteile, die Go bietet gibt es in Deutschland verhältnismäßig wenige Entwickler, die sich selber als „Gopher“ bezeichnen.

Wir wollen euch mit dem Golang Meetup die Sprache näher bringen und bei Interesse eine aktive Go-Community im Breisgau ins Leben rufen. Als Starthilfe haben wir uns einen Go-Experten aus München eingeladen.

Speaker:
Oliver Eilhard - „Oliver is a passionate programmer who fell in love with Go when it was released in 2012. Since then, he brought several Go-based applications into production. As an avid fan of Open Source, he maintains Elastic, the most commonly used Go client for Elasticsearch. In this meetup, he will talk about various topics he learned on his journey of working with Go professionally.“

<a>https://www.xing.com/profile/Oliver_Eilhard</a>;
<a>https://github.com/olivere</a>;

Host: 
iTernity GmbH 
www.iTernity.com

events.name: Creating Apps using Firebase
events.description:
Topic: Demonstration of Firebase features - Auth, Realtime Database, Firebase Storage and Functions

We will demonstrate the features using an example showcase app.

In this meetup, we will show how easy it is to program an app using Firebase. First, we will demonstrate how one can use Firebase Auth and Firebase Auth UI to easily allow users to authenticate to the app. Then, we'll check out how to store data in the Firebase Realtime Database and how to use Firebase Functions with MailJet to send an email, when new data is inserted into the database. Finally, there will be a demonstration about how to store images using Firebase Storage. In the end, there will be an open discussion with Pizza and drinks ;-)

Speaker: Jerome Meinke
events.how_to_find_us: The conference room is in the Kagan tower -> 4th floor. The entrance is on the right side of the central station :)

events.name: Project Feedback Meetup
events.description: Every developer will get a 5 min slot to present his project to the others and an additional 10 min to discuss and gather feedback for the project.

events.name: UI-/UX-Design for Websites and Apps
events.description:
1. Was ist UI/UX-Design?
- Unterschiede von UI und UX-Design

2. Wie funktionieren UI/UX Design zusammen?
- Wie man UI und UX-Design miteinander verknüpft

3. Was ist die Wirkung von gutem bzw. schlechtem UI/UX Design?
- Was für gewollte bzw. ungewollte Effekte durch UI/UX-Design entstehen können

4. Woran kann man gutes UI/UX-Design erkennen?

5. Résumé

Speaker: Semih Volkert

events.name: Home automation: Self-made vacuum cleaner robot
events.description:
The presentation "Home automation: Self-made vacuum cleaner robot" is about a private project of building an Arduino-based vacuum cleaner robot. Although a short introduction to the Arduino platform will be given, the talk won't dive too deep into technical details. The main focus will be on presenting the general idea of the robot and showing on a higher level, how the different functionalities of the robot can be realized. One goal of this talk is to motivate the audience to build self-made smart home devices with Arduino or comparable technologies themselves. In the end there will be enough time for a discussion and an exchange of ideas and suggestions as well as a short demo of the prototype of the robot.

Speaker: Alexander Haberstroh
events.how_to_find_us: We are meeting in the Kagan tower (Bismarckallee 9) in the 4th floor. There is no door bell, so please be there on time. Otherwise we will hang out sheets of paper with a phone number to reach us.

events.name: Networking-Event
events.description:
We are meeting up at the Biergarten of the Brauerei Feierling in the city center of Freiburg.

This is going to be a networking event for people who are interested in developing of exciting projects.

Everyone is invited to bring his / her laptop and to present to the others a project which he / she is working on to get feedback.

If there are not enough places in the Biergarten, we will change location to the Kastaniengarten.
events.how_to_find_us: Meet us at the entrance of the Beer garden (Brauerei Feierling)

events.name: Developer Breakfast
events.description:
Our Developer Breakfast might become a regular chin-wag we host in order to share experiences, vent constructively and naturally build a Freiburg community of developers, creatives, designers and technically-minded entrepreneurs.

We aim to continue to breakdown barriers and to encourage knowledge sharing, with the long-term goal of supporting the growth and development of the region’s creative and digital sector.

This is the first developer breakfast we are organizing. Here is the breakfast menu: http://www.brasil-freiburg.de/fruehstueck.php
Depending on how many people would like to join us, we might change the location.
events.how_to_find_us: We will be sitting at tables in the non-smoking area.
